{
  "stem": "18102.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Ours didn't get hit but-- and my father was right that the edge of the city was not strafed or bombed, and, and it was all more or less pointed for inside the city.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And of course Poland fell in seven days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There wasn't much need for a lot of bombing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I didn't see any of it myself until after the fact.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, as a member of the city council, the mayor and the city council had met.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in their discussion right directly as after war broke out, probably the very first day, they decided-- or it was the decision of the council-- that the entire council as well as all other prominent city folk-- mens folk-- should leave because it was rumored, and I learned later correctly rumored, that the Germans, once they entered the city, would use the city councilmen and other prominent city officials or people as hostages should anything go wrong in the city.",
      "word_count": 81
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In other words, if some order of the German army was violated, then they would be held accountable and be shot. 10 of them would be shot, or five of them would be shot in retribution.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this was a accepted principle that they believed-- they, the city council and the mayor-- believed would happen.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so they decided that if they left the city, they couldn't be arrested for this hostage purpose.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so it was agreed that they would rent the vans and on a given night-- actually, in the middle of the night-- they left in a van for parts unknown.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I never knew, my mother never knew, where they left.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But they were obviously fleeing from Poland, which was invaded by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So it was an idea to get away from Poland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well--",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
